By Taiye Agbaje The indigenes of Plateau living in the U.S., on Wednesday, called on the citizens of the state to unite together towards a peaceful society. The group, under the auspices of the Plateau State Association USA, Inc. (PSA-USA, Inc), gave the charge when its newly elected president, Dr Barth Shepkong, delivered a speech at a swearing-in ceremony of the executive members. The statement, signed by the public relations officer of the body, Mrs Francisca Keyen, was made available to newsmen in Abuja. “We call on Plateau citizens both at home and abroad to unite behind a peaceful and prosperous Plateau,” Shepkong said. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-43889" src="https://www.nannews.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220511-WA0022-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://www.nannews.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220511-WA0022-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.nannews.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220511-WA0022-682x1024.jpg 682w, https://www.nannews.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220511-WA0022-768x1153.jpg 768w, https://www.nannews.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220511-WA0022-1023x1536.jpg 1023w, https://www.nannews.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220511-WA0022-1024x1537.jpg 1024w, https://www.nannews.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220511-WA0022-scaled.jpg 419w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /> Dr Barth Shepkong He said the association was a non-political, non-religious association organised exclusively for charitable, scientific, and educational purposes. He also said it was established specifically to engage in education, health, social and economic development activities for the poor, disabled and underprivileged in Plateau and those living in the U.S. “On behalf of the executive committee, we are truly humbled by this vote of confidence, and we promise to take the organisation to greater heights,” the president said. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that other newly elected officials of PSA-USA, Inc are Lady Gertrude Longwan, Vice-President and Mr Nanjul Wuyep, as General Secretary. They also include Mr Nenshang Ngo, Social Secretary; Mrs. Asabe L Spencer-Mhya, CPA, as Treasurer and Mrs Keyen as Public Relations Officer. NAN reports that the executive members of PSA-USA, Inc, who were sworn-in on May 2, will serve a two-year term.(NAN)www.nannews.ng